# MANIFEST.in — graft non-package files into the setuptools source distribution.
#
# setuptools' sdist reads this file to pick up files that live OUTSIDE the
# Python packages declared in pyproject.toml's [tool.setuptools] packages list.
# ap2's operator manual (agentskills.io SKILL.md bundles) lives at `ap2/skills/`
# (TB-422 relocated it under the package so it ships as installed package-data in
# the wheel, not only the sdist). package-data already carries it in the sdist,
# but this graft makes the operator-manual inclusion explicit alongside the
# top-level docs an outside consumer needs in a clean `python -m build --sdist`.

# Operator manual: the skills tree, now under the ap2 package.
graft ap2/skills

# Top-level docs an outside consumer needs.
include README.md
include LICENSE
include CHANGELOG.md

# Architecture doc (also wheel package-data via ap2/*.md; included here so the
# sdist carries it explicitly alongside the rest of the docs).
include ap2/architecture.md
